BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Byte vs Brain: Exploring the Promise and Perils of Artificial Inte
 lligence
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260318T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260318T200000
UID:bd3655e652838dcfbdfb29bc0d1b8557@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, STEM\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nArtificial Intelligence
  is no longer the stuff of science fiction--it’s in our pockets\, our wo
 rkplaces\, and our newsfeeds. But as these "bytes" become more sophisticat
 ed\, how do they measure up against the human "brain"?Join an expert from 
 F&M’s Computer Science department as we peel back the curtain on the wor
 ld of generative AI. We’ll explore the incredible promises of this techn
 ology—from revolutionizing medical research and accessibility to superch
 arging daily productivity—while honestly confronting its perils\, includ
 ing deepfakes\, data privacy\, and the "hallucinations" of digital minds.W
 hether you’re a tech enthusiast\, a curious skeptic\, or just someone wo
 ndering what ChatGPT is all about\, this program offers a space to separat
 e the science from the fiction 💻Registration is encouraged 💻
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center B
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/reserved-adult-servicesp
 rogram-162122
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
