BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Teen Book Talk: The School for Good and Evil
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260323T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260323T190000
UID:602966df641706854bb1ef419f7bf7fb@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Book Club\, Teens\n\nFor Teens ages 13-18 years of age only.Ca
 lling all teen readers! Join us for Teen Book Talk\, a fun and engaging mo
 nthly book discussion group led by members of our Teen Advisory Board! Boo
 k selections are chosen by teens during advisory meetings. Interested in j
 oining the Teen Advisory Board? Sign up through the library calendar. Each
  month\, we’ll dive into a new title—ranging from trending young adult
  fiction to graphic novels\, fantasy epics\, thought-provoking contemporar
 y stories\, and more.This month\, we'll be reading (this soon to be a moti
 on picture) "The School for Good and Evil" by Soman Chainani.  What if you
  knew you were meant for the School of Good but got placed in the School o
 f Evil?  What if you knew you were meant for the School of Evil but were p
 laced in the School of Good?  Follow Sophie and Agatha as they navigate th
 eir way through their schools and learn who they really are.  You’ll get
  the chance to share your thoughts\, hear different perspectives\, and con
 nect with fellow book lovers in a relaxed and welcoming space. Snacks will
  be provided\, and occasionally we’ll have themed activities or giveaway
 s tied to the book!Note: To help everyone stay present and get the most ou
 t of the experience\, we ask that all phones stay in pockets or bags durin
 g the program. Thank you for your cooperation!Library Program PoliciesNo S
 how – Patrons failing to cancel their registration for more than 2 libra
 ry programs in a month will be restricted from registering for future prog
 rams for a period of one month’s time. Please cancel your registrations 
 at least 2 hours prior to the start of the program to allow for those on t
 he waiting list to be notified of their change in registration status.Late
  Arrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior to the start of the program t
 o allow for parking and other circumstances. The program will begin prompt
 ly at the designated time. At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to t
 hose on the wait list who will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registr
 ants may be allowed into the program. However\, registrants will not be pe
 rmitted to enter the program 5 minutes past the start time.Check In - All 
 participants must provide an emergency contact number upon registration or
  at the start of the program.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Study Room #119
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/teen-book-talk-156956
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
