BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sensory Discovery Storytime
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260325T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260325T150000
UID:cb646f31a35f5fecfa327413df147eea@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Storytime\, Children\n\nJoin Ms. Laura for a fun and engaging 
 sensory discovery storytime program all about Rainbows! We will review col
 ors\, do some color mixing\, make a walking rainbow and explore a sensory 
 bin! This program is intended for children 3-6 years old. Children should 
 be able to listen to\, comprehend and participate in emergent science\, ma
 th and literacy topics. Activities may include small parts so children sho
 uld be past the stage of mouthing items. Parents and caregivers are invite
 d to participate with their children to learn how to replicate the activit
 ies at home!Sensory experiences provide children with opportunities to dev
 elop fine motor skills\, eye-hand coordination\, problem solving\, logic a
 nd concentration. They'll grow their attention spans and practice emotiona
 l regulation and mindfulness. Parents and caregivers are invited to partic
 ipate with their children to learn how to replicate the activities at home
 !Allergy notice: Please note sensory materials may contain allergens like 
 wheat.Ms. Laura has over 20 years of preschool classroom experience bringi
 ng a wealth of knowledge in early childhood development. Her approach focu
 ses on creating a warm\, engaging\, and supportive environment where child
 ren can thrive.Adults attending with their child(ren) do NOT need to regis
 ter. Please add any additional registrants to your registration if more th
 an one child that will be participating in the program.Registration will o
 pen at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, March 11th for Manheim Township and East Lamp
 eter residents and on Friday\, March 13th for residents of other municipal
 ities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show – Patrons failing to cancel their regist
 ration for more than 2 library programs in a month will be restricted from
  registering for future programs for a period of one month’s time. Pleas
 e cancel your registrations at least 2 hours prior to the start of the pro
 gram to allow for those on the waiting list to be notified of their change
  in registration status.Late Arrivals – Please arrive 10 minutes prior t
 o the start of the program to allow for parking and other circumstances. T
 he program will begin promptly at the designated time. At this time\, your
  spot will be forfeited to those on the wait list who will be granted entr
 y. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed into the program. However\
 , registrants will not be permitted to enter the program 5 minutes past th
 e start time.Accompanying Adults – This program is for adults and childr
 en to enjoy together. Please plan to attend and be engaged with your child
 . Drop offs will not be permitted.Cancellations- Please check your email p
 rior to departing to verify that the program has not been cancelled.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Morgan Center AB
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/sensory-discovery-storyt
 ime-160167
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
