BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Author Talk: Jeff Bogle's Street Cats & Where to Find Them
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260325T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260325T200000
UID:ae97a2766a5a79f15e1d80679c84931f@calendar.lancasterlibraries.org
DESCRIPTION:Community\, Presentation\, Everyone\n\nJoin us as we welcome a
 uthor and photographer Jeff Bogle with his new book\, Street Cats and Wher
 e to Find Them: The Most Feline-Friendly Cities and Attractions Around the
  WorldDuring this engaging\, all-ages presentation\, Jeff will talk about 
 the making of his book\, Street Cats & Where to Find Them\, the world's fi
 rst travel guide book for cat lovers\, read selections from the book\, dis
 cuss the first-ever street cat cruise he is hosting in Europe later this y
 ear\, and take your questions\, all while hundreds of his photos of cats a
 round the world play behind him. There will also be an opportunity to meet
  Jeff\, buy a copy of his book\, and have it signed.All ages welcome • R
 egistration is requiredBio: Jeff is the author of the travel book\, Street
  Cats and Where to Find Them. He's a dad of two daughters\, an avid travel
 er\, an award-winning photographer and a freelance writer who lives in the
  suburbs of Philadelphia with his wife and their cats. He's written storie
 s for BBC Travel\, the Washington Post\, Good Housekeeping\, Parents Magaz
 ine\, Fodor's\, Wine Enthusiast\, Esquire\, Real Simple\, and Reader’s D
 igest\, among other print and online publications. Jeff is also the founde
 r and publisher of the quarterly literary magazine and small book press\, 
 Stanchion.
LOCATION:Lancaster\, LPL Community + Board Room
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/author-talk-jeff-bogles-
 street-cats-where-find-them-157547
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
END:VEVENT
