DESCRIPTION:Book Club\, Adults\, Seniors\n\nStart your Wednesday with a si
 de of storytelling. The MTPL Book Discussion Group meets the 2nd Wednesday
  of each month at 10am to explore new worlds together. It’s more than ju
 st a book club—it’s your monthly morning retreat for thoughtful talk a
 nd local connection. We’ve got the books\; we just need you!Please regis
 ter for each meeting\, as it allows the library to update you if there are
  any changes to a meeting due to weather delays\, closures\, or other circ
 umstances.January 14: 1984 by George OrwellFebruary 11: Empire of AI by Ka
 ren HaoMarch 11: The Greatest Generation by Tom BrokawApril 8: West with G
 iraffes by Lynda RutledgeMay 13: Klara and the Sun by Kazuo IshiguroJune 1
