 is a wonderful opportunity for families to bond\, build literacy skills\, 
 and create lasting memories together!Adults attending with their child(ren
 ) do NOT need to register. Please add any additional registrants to your r
 egistration if more than one child that will be participating in the progr
 am.Registration will open at 9:00AM on Wednesday\, Arpil 1st for Manheim T
 ownship and East Lampeter residents and on Friday\, April 3rd for resident
 s of other municipalities.Storytime PoliciesNo Show – Patrons failing to
  cancel their registration for more than 2 library programs in a month wil
 l be restricted from registering for future programs for a period of one m
 onth’s time. Please cancel your registrations at least 2 hours prior to 
 the start of the program to allow for those on the waiting list to be noti
 fied of their change in registration status.Late Arrivals – Please arriv
 e 10 minutes prior to the start of the program to allow for parking and ot
 her circumstances. The program will begin promptly at the designated time.
  At this time\, your spot will be forfeited to those on the wait list who 
 will be granted entry. If spots remain\, registrants may be allowed into t
 he program. However\, registrants will not be permitted to enter the progr
 am 5 minutes past the start time.Accompanying Adults – This program is f
 or adults and children to enjoy together. Please plan to attend and be eng
 aged with your child. Drop offs will not be permitted.Cancellations- Pleas
 e check your email prior to departing to verify that the program has not b
 een cancelled.
LOCATION:Manheim Township\, MTP Lapp Story Silo
URL:https://calendar.lancasterlibraries.org/event/family-story-time-148969
X-SOURCE:Lancaster Libraries
